# Who can do what (Retail HR app)

## Two different ideas

- **Store lead (per store)** = who is officially in charge of that store on the **Stores** page (`/locations`). Stored as `locations.manager_employee_id`. It is **org chart data**, not “what buttons they see in the app.”
- **Product admin powers** = what someone can **click** in the app (schedule, time clock, user list, etc.). For Store Managers this is mostly driven by `employees.admin_access` plus their role.

## Organization Owner

- A few people (1–3) are **Owners** in the database: `employees.role` is **`Owner`**, **`Org Owner`**, or **`Organization Owner`** (see `lib/rbac/matrix.ts`).
- They get permission **`org.owner`** (`PERMISSIONS.ORG_OWNER`).
- **Only Owners can:** promote someone to Store Manager, and change another Store Manager’s **Permissions** (module toggles / `admin_access`).
- **Store Managers** can still do day-to-day people tasks where the app allows (e.g. bulk add / edit users) if they have **`users.manage`**; they **cannot** promote admins or edit `admin_access` for others.

## Stores page

- **Nav:** Dashboard → **Stores** (`/locations`).
- Lists each **location** and a **Store lead** dropdown.
- When **`RBAC_ENABLED=true`**, only **Owners** can change the dropdown; others see read-only text.

## RBAC switch

- **`RBAC_ENABLED=true`**: rules above apply; match login email to `employees.email`.
- **`RBAC_ENABLED`** unset/false: dev-friendly “full access” in code paths that check RBAC — do **not** rely on this for production.

## Migration to apply for store leads

- `017_locations_store_manager.sql` adds `locations.manager_employee_id`.

## Security audit (governance trail)

- `018_security_audit_log.sql` adds `security_audit_events`.
- Owner actions append rows: admin permission changes, promotions, store lead changes, organization owner changes.
- **Security audit** nav item (`/security-audit`) is **Owner-only** (`org.owner`).

## Log out & assigning owners in the UI

- **Log out:** header **avatar / name** (top right) opens the account menu → **Log out**. Session is shown whenever `user` exists (not only when email is present).
- **Organization owner:** on an employee **profile** (`/users/[id]`), owners see **Organization owner** checkbox; grant/remove is audited. **Bootstrap:** the first owner must be set once in Supabase (`employees.role = 'Org Owner'`) so someone has `org.owner` before the in-app toggle works.
